"title": "3233: Holy Spirit, and sanctification",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "3233",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The work of the Holy Spirit in enabling believers to lead holy lives, dedicated to the service of God and conformed to his likeness.</p>\n<h2>The Spirit of holiness is promised</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:11\">MAT 3:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:16\">LUK 3:16</a> <em>“fire” implies the Holy Spirit's work of purification and judgment.</em></p>\n<h2>Sanctification is a special work of the Holy Spirit</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:16\">ROM 15:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:11\">1CO 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:5\">GAL 5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:2</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit requires believers to be sanctified</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13\">2TH 2:13</a></strong> <em>Sanctification is a necessary part of being a Christian.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:18-1Cor6:19\">1CO 6:18–6:19</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit enables believers to be sanctified</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:4\">ROM 8:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:13\">ROM 8:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:18\">EPH 5:18</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit produces sanctification</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:22-Gal5:23\">GAL 5:22–5:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:17\">ROM 14:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:7\">2TI 1:7</a></p>\n<h2>The process of sanctification</h2>\n<h3>The Holy Spirit makes believers more like Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:18</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The Holy Spirit helps mortify sinful human nature</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:13\">ROM 8:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:17\">GAL 5:17</a></p>\n<h3>The Holy Spirit is opposed to natural desires</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16-Gal5:17\">GAL 5:16–5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:5-Rom8:9\">ROM 8:5–8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:19\">JUD 1:19</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of people sanctified by the Holy Spirit</h2>\n<p>Joshua:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:18\">NUM 27:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:9\">DEU 34:9</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:25\">LUK 2:25</a> <em>Simeon</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:3\">ACT 6:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:5\">ACT 6:5</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:24\">ACT 11:24</a> <em>Barnabas</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:6\">2CO 6:6</a> <em>Paul and his companions</em></p>",
